# Changelog

All notable changes to **Onto3D** derived from the provided files (`v0.1` ‚Üí `v1.0`).  
Versioning follows **SemVer**: `MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH`.

## [1.0] - 2025-10-10
New Features

#### Multi-language Support: Added English language option alongside Italian
Language Persistence: Language preference now saved in localStorage and persists across sessions
Enhanced Navigation: New language switcher in header for easy switching between IT/EN

#### UI/UX Improvements
Responsive Design Enhancements: Improved mobile layout and touch interactions
Visual Polish: Updated color scheme with better contrast and modern aesthetics
Interactive Elements: Added hover effects and smooth transitions throughout the interface
Loading States: Implemented proper loading indicators for better user feedback

#### Technical Improvements
Code Refactoring: Cleaned up component structure and improved code organization
Performance Optimization: Reduced unnecessary re-renders and improved overall performance
Error Handling: Added comprehensive error handling for edge cases
Accessibility: Improved keyboard navigation and screen reader support

#### Bug Fixes
Fixed image URL handling and loading issues
Resolved spacing inconsistencies in mobile view
Corrected translation inconsistencies across the application
Fixed localStorage persistence issues

#### Content Updates
Updated product descriptions and feature highlights
Refined copy for better clarity in both languages
Added missing translations for new features

## [0.5] - 2025-10-05
### üß© Node ‚Üî Geometry Integration & Enhanced UI

#### Highlights
- Full **bidirectional link system** between Onto3D nodes and 3D geometries.  
  Connections can be created, updated, and removed while maintaining synchronization both ways.
- Unified **Viewport and Node Editor integration** through coordinated panels.

#### New Features
- ** Geometry Connection Panel**
  - Added ‚ÄúConnect Geometry‚Äù section in the Node Editor N-Panel.
  - Commands for *Create Connection*, *Break Connection*, and *Update Links*.
  - Displays a clear list of linked geometries.
  - Warning indicator when linked objects are renamed or missing.

- ** 3D Viewport Panel ‚Äî ‚ÄúLinked Node Info‚Äù**
  - Shows node information directly in the 3D Viewport for the selected object.
  - Displays node name, type, and key properties (Title, Description, IRI, etc.).
  - Added buttons:
    - **Open IRI** ‚Üí Opens the node‚Äôs IRI/URL in the default browser.  
    - **Frame Linked Node (.)** ‚Üí Centers the linked node in the Node Editor.

- **ü™ê Node Editor Improvements**
  - Added **Frame Selected** and **Isolate Selected** buttons inside nodes, acting on linked geometries.
  - Safe context handling (`temp_override`) for all viewport operations.
  - Reorganized N-Panel sections (*Info* and *Connect Geometry*), removed obsolete *Quick IRI*.

#### Structural & Code Improvements
- Modularized add-on: `__init__.py`, `nodes.py`, `ui_panels.py`, and `preferences_ontology.py`.
- Hidden internal properties (`onto3d_ontology`, `onto3d_entity_id`, `onto3d_property_id`, `onto3d_links`) from UI.
- Removed automatic display of custom properties.
- Improved `Open IRI`:
  - Detects multiple field names (`onto3d_iri`, `iri`, `url`).
  - Adds `https://` automatically if the scheme is missing.
- Version-safe implementation of Local View toggle and View Selected operators.

#### Developer Notes
- GitHub Actions workflow: `Build add-on ZIP`
  - Automatically zips `onto3d/` on tag push (`v*`) and uploads as release asset.
  - Produces `onto3d-v0.5.zip` installable via *Preferences ‚Üí Add-ons ‚Üí Install ‚Ä¶*
- Compatible with **Blender 4.5 +**

#### üß° Contributors
- **Giacomo Mancuso** ‚Äî concept, ontology modelling, UX direction  
- **ChatGPT (OpenAI)** ‚Äî Python implementation, UI architecture, automation setup

## [0.4.2] - 2025-10-04
### Added
- **Open IRI in Browser**: new operator `onto3d.open_iri` to open the resource IRI in the system browser (button on the node and in the *Item* panel).

### Changed
- Minor UI/text refinements.

## [0.4.1] - 2025-10-04
### Added
- **View helpers** in the Node Editor:
  - `onto3d.toggle_sync_views` (sync views),
  - `onto3d.node_zoom_node` (frame selected node),
  - `onto3d.node_zoom_geometry` (frame linked geometry),
  - `onto3d.node_isolate_geometry` (isolate/show only linked geometry).
- **Panel `ONTO3D_PT_ItemProperties`** (N-Panel *Item* section) for node-context tools.

### Changed
- Minor panel tweaks.

## [0.3.0]
### Added
- **Connect Geometry**: new panel `ONTO3D_PT_ConnectGeometry` with operators:
  - `onto3d.create_connection` (link entity node ‚Üí one or more objects; supports groups under **Empty**),
  - `onto3d.break_connection` (unlink),
  - `onto3d.update_connections` (refresh connection list).

## [0.2.0]
### Added
- **Ontology-driven presets**:
  - `cidoc.generate_presets` (populate Add-menu with classes/properties),
  - `cidoc.clear_presets` (clear presets),
  - `cidoc.reload_addon` (quick reload).
### Changed
- **N-Panel tab renamed**: from **CIDOC** to **Onto3D**.

## [0.1.0]
### Added
- **Initial CIDOC-like graph setup**:
  - in/out sockets, *Entity* and *Property* nodes, *GraphTree*.
- **Ontology management** (via lazy `rdflib` import):
  - `cidoc.import_ontology`, `cidoc.remove_namespace`, `cidoc.export_namespace`.
- **Panel** `CIDOC_PT_OntologiesPanel` for import & namespaces.

---

### Notes
- Version mapping for the uploaded files:  
  `v01 ‚Üí 0.1.0`, `v02 ‚Üí 0.2.0`, `v03 ‚Üí 0.3.0`, `v04_1 ‚Üí 0.4.1`, `v04_2 ‚Üí 0.4.2`.
- Dates reflect the day this changelog was compiled.
- Distribution for Blender: create a ZIP with a **single top-level package folder** (e.g., `onto3d/`) and attach it to **Releases**.
